# MarktMap

Standalone export of the MarktMap marketing site. Built with TanStack Start (React 19 + Vite 7 + Tailwind v4).

## Local development (VS Code)

Requires Node.js 20+ (or Bun).

```bash
npm install        # or: bun install
npm run dev        # starts dev server (http://localhost:8080 by default)
npm run build      # production build → .output/
npm run preview    # preview the production build
```

Open the project folder in VS Code, install dependencies, then run `npm run dev`.

## Deploy on Vercel

1. Push this folder to a Git repository (GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket).
2. Import the repo on https://vercel.com/new.
3. Vercel auto-detects TanStack Start (Vite). Defaults:
   - Build Command: `npm run build`
   - Output Directory: `.output/public`
4. Click **Deploy**. No environment variables required.

Alternatively, use Vercel CLI:

```bash
npm i -g vercel
vercel
```

## Project structure

- `src/routes/` – file-based routes (each page = own URL)
- `src/components/` – shared UI components
- `src/styles.css` – Tailwind v4 entry + design tokens
- `src/assets/` – images bundled with the build

The site is fully static; no backend/database required.
